The paper deals with distributed data streams and presents fully distributed algorithms for random sampling. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with databases (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG) concepts such as reservoir sampling and experimental evaluation. Finally, the paper also discusses theoretical analysis and promises further scaling, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
